44CachedRawResource::CachedRawResource(CachedResourceRequest&& request, Type type, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar)
45 : CachedResource(WTFMove(request), type, sessionID, cookieJar)
46 , m_identifier(0)
47 , m_allowEncodedDataReplacement(true)
48{
49 ASSERT(isMainOrMediaOrIconOrRawResource());
50}
51
52std::optional<SharedBufferDataView> CachedRawResource::calculateIncrementalDataChunk(const SharedBuffer* data) const
53{
54 size_t previousDataLength = encodedSize();
55 if (!data || data->size() <= previousDataLength)
56 return std::nullopt;
57 return data->getSomeData(previousDataLength);
58}
59
60void CachedRawResource::updateBuffer(SharedBuffer& data)
61{
62 // Skip any updateBuffers triggered from nested runloops. We'll have the complete buffer in finishLoading.
63 if (m_inIncrementalDataNotify)
64 return;
65
66 CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource> protectedThis(this);
67 ASSERT(dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::BufferData);
68 m_data = &data;
69
70 auto previousDataSize = encodedSize();
71 while (data.size() > previousDataSize) {
72 auto incrementalData = data.getSomeData(previousDataSize);
73 previousDataSize += incrementalData.size();
74
75 SetForScope<bool> notifyScope(m_inIncrementalDataNotify, true);
76 notifyClientsDataWasReceived(incrementalData.data(), incrementalData.size());
77 }
78 setEncodedSize(data.size());
79
80 if (dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData) {
81 if (m_loader)
82 m_loader->setDataBufferingPolicy(DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData);
83 clear();
84 } else
85 CachedResource::updateBuffer(data);
86
87 if (m_delayedFinishLoading) {
88 auto delayedFinishLoading = std::exchange(m_delayedFinishLoading, std::nullopt);
89 finishLoading(delayedFinishLoading->buffer.get(), { });
90 }
91}
92
93void CachedRawResource::updateData(const uint8_t* data, unsigned length)
94{
95 ASSERT(dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData);
96 notifyClientsDataWasReceived(data, length);
97 CachedResource::updateData(data, length);
98}
99
100void CachedRawResource::finishLoading(SharedBuffer* data, const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
101{
102 if (m_inIncrementalDataNotify) {
103 // We may get here synchronously from updateBuffer() if the callback there ends up spinning a runloop.
104 // In that case delay the call.
105 m_delayedFinishLoading = std::make_optional(DelayedFinishLoading { data });
106 return;
107 };
108 CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource> protectedThis(this);
109 DataBufferingPolicy dataBufferingPolicy = this->dataBufferingPolicy();
110 if (dataBufferingPolicy == DataBufferingPolicy::BufferData) {
111 m_data = data;
112
113 if (auto incrementalData = calculateIncrementalDataChunk(data)) {
114 setEncodedSize(data->size());
115 notifyClientsDataWasReceived(incrementalData->data(), incrementalData->size());
116 }
117 }
118
119#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
120 m_allowEncodedDataReplacement = m_loader && !m_loader->isQuickLookResource();
121#endif
122
123 CachedResource::finishLoading(data, metrics);
124 if (dataBufferingPolicy == DataBufferingPolicy::BufferData && this->dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData) {
125 if (m_loader)
126 m_loader->setDataBufferingPolicy(DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData);
127 clear();
128 }
129}
130
131void CachedRawResource::notifyClientsDataWasReceived(const uint8_t* data, unsigned length)
132{
133 if (!length)
134 return;
135
136 CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource> protectedThis(this);
137 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient> w(m_clients);
138 while (CachedRawResourceClient* c = w.next())
139 c->dataReceived(*this, data, length);
140}

142static void iterateRedirects(CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource>&& handle, CachedRawResourceClient& client, Vector<std::pair<ResourceRequest, ResourceResponse>>&& redirectsInReverseOrder, CompletionHandler<void(ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
143{
144 if (!handle->hasClient(client) || redirectsInReverseOrder.isEmpty())
145 return completionHandler({ });
146 auto redirectPair = redirectsInReverseOrder.takeLast();
147 client.redirectReceived(*handle, WTFMove(redirectPair.first), WTFMove(redirectPair.second), [handle = WTFMove(handle), client, redirectsInReverseOrder = WTFMove(redirectsInReverseOrder), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (ResourceRequest&&) mutable {
148 // Ignore the new request because we can't do anything with it.
149 // We're just replying a redirect chain that has already happened.
150 iterateRedirects(WTFMove(handle), client, WTFMove(redirectsInReverseOrder), WTFMove(completionHandler));
151 });
152}
153
154void CachedRawResource::didAddClient(CachedResourceClient& c)
155{
156 CachedRawResourceClient& client = static_cast<CachedRawResourceClient&>(c);
157 size_t redirectCount = m_redirectChain.size();
158 Vector<std::pair<ResourceRequest, ResourceResponse>> redirectsInReverseOrder;
159 redirectsInReverseOrder.reserveInitialCapacity(redirectCount);
160 for (size_t i = 0; i < redirectCount; ++i) {
161 const auto& pair = m_redirectChain[redirectCount - i - 1];
162 redirectsInReverseOrder.uncheckedAppend(std::make_pair(pair.m_request, pair.m_redirectResponse));
163 }
164 iterateRedirects(CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource>(this), client, WTFMove(redirectsInReverseOrder), [this, protectedThis = CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource>(this), client = &client] (ResourceRequest&&) mutable {
165 if (!hasClient(*client))
166 return;
167 auto responseProcessedHandler = [this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), client] {
168 if (!hasClient(*client))
169 return;
170 if (m_data) {
171 m_data->forEachSegment([&](auto& segment) {
172 client->dataReceived(*this, segment.data(), segment.size());
173 });
174 }
175 if (!hasClient(*client))
176 return;
177 CachedResource::didAddClient(*client);
178 };
179
180 if (!m_response.isNull()) {
181 ResourceResponse response(m_response);
182 if (validationCompleting())
183 response.setSource(ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCacheAfterValidation);
184 else {
185 ASSERT(!validationInProgress());
186 response.setSource(ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCache);
187 }
188 client->responseReceived(*this, response, WTFMove(responseProcessedHandler));
189 } else
190 responseProcessedHandler();
191 });
192}
193
194void CachedRawResource::allClientsRemoved()
195{
196 if (m_loader)
197 m_loader->cancelIfNotFinishing();
198}
199
200static void iterateClients(CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient>&& walker, CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource>&& handle, ResourceRequest&& request, std::unique_ptr<ResourceResponse>&& response, CompletionHandler<void(ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
201{
202 auto client = walker.next();
203 if (!client)
204 return completionHandler(WTFMove(request));
205 const ResourceResponse& responseReference = *response;
206 client->redirectReceived(*handle, WTFMove(request), responseReference, [walker = WTFMove(walker), handle = WTFMove(handle), response = WTFMove(response), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (ResourceRequest&& request) mutable {
207 iterateClients(WTFMove(walker), WTFMove(handle), WTFMove(request), WTFMove(response), WTFMove(completionHandler));
208 });
209}
210
211void CachedRawResource::redirectReceived(ResourceRequest&& request, const ResourceResponse& response, CompletionHandler<void(ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
212{
213 RELEASE_LOG_ALWAYS("redirectReceived:");
214 if (response.isNull())
215 CachedResource::redirectReceived(WTFMove(request), response, WTFMove(completionHandler));
216 else {
217 m_redirectChain.append(RedirectPair(request, response));
218 iterateClients(CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient>(m_clients), CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource>(this), WTFMove(request), makeUnique<ResourceResponse>(response), [this, protectedThis = CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource>(this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), response] (ResourceRequest&& request) mutable {
219 CachedResource::redirectReceived(WTFMove(request), response, WTFMove(completionHandler));
220 });
221 }
222}
223
224void CachedRawResource::responseReceived(const ResourceResponse& response)
225{
226 CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource> protectedThis(this);
227 if (!m_identifier)
228 m_identifier = m_loader->identifier();
229 CachedResource::responseReceived(response);
230 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient> w(m_clients);
231 while (CachedRawResourceClient* c = w.next())
232 c->responseReceived(*this, m_response, nullptr);
233}
234
235bool CachedRawResource::shouldCacheResponse(const ResourceResponse& response)
236{
237 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient> w(m_clients);
238 while (CachedRawResourceClient* c = w.next()) {
239 if (!c->shouldCacheResponse(*this, response))
240 return false;
241 }
242 return true;
243}

245void CachedRawResource::didSendData(unsigned long long bytesSent, unsigned long long totalBytesToBeSent)
246{
247 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient> w(m_clients);
248 while (CachedRawResourceClient* c = w.next())
249 c->dataSent(*this, bytesSent, totalBytesToBeSent);
250}

252void CachedRawResource::finishedTimingForWorkerLoad(ResourceTiming&& resourceTiming)
253{
254 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient> w(m_clients);
255 while (CachedRawResourceClient* c = w.next())
256 c->finishedTimingForWorkerLoad(*this, resourceTiming);
257}

259void CachedRawResource::switchClientsToRevalidatedResource()
260{
261 ASSERT(m_loader);
262 // If we're in the middle of a successful revalidation, responseReceived() hasn't been called, so we haven't set m_identifier.
263 ASSERT(!m_identifier);
264 downcast<CachedRawResource>(*resourceToRevalidate()).m_identifier = m_loader->identifier();
265 CachedResource::switchClientsToRevalidatedResource();
266}

268void CachedRawResource::setDefersLoading(bool defers)
269{
270 if (m_loader)
271 m_loader->setDefersLoading(defers);
272}

276 m_options.dataBufferingPolicy = dataBufferingPolicy;

279static bool shouldIgnoreHeaderForCacheReuse(HTTPHeaderName name)
280{
281 switch (name) {
282 // FIXME: This list of headers that don't affect cache policy almost certainly isn't complete.
283 case HTTPHeaderName::Accept:
284 case HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl:
285 case HTTPHeaderName::Pragma:
286 case HTTPHeaderName::Purpose:
287 case HTTPHeaderName::Referer:
288 case HTTPHeaderName::UserAgent:
289 return true;
290
291 default:
292 return false;
293 }
294}
295
296bool CachedRawResource::canReuse(const ResourceRequest& newRequest) const
297{
298 if (dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData)
299 return false;
300
301 if (m_resourceRequest.httpMethod() != newRequest.httpMethod())
302 return false;
303
304 if (m_resourceRequest.httpBody() != newRequest.httpBody())
305 return false;
306
307 if (m_resourceRequest.allowCookies() != newRequest.allowCookies())
308 return false;
309
310 if (newRequest.isConditional())
311 return false;
312
313 // Ensure most headers match the existing headers before continuing.
314 // Note that the list of ignored headers includes some headers explicitly related to caching.
315 // A more detailed check of caching policy will be performed later, this is simply a list of
316 // headers that we might permit to be different and still reuse the existing CachedResource.
317 const HTTPHeaderMap& newHeaders = newRequest.httpHeaderFields();
318 const HTTPHeaderMap& oldHeaders = m_resourceRequest.httpHeaderFields();
319
320 for (const auto& header : newHeaders) {
321 if (header.keyAsHTTPHeaderName) {
322 if (!shouldIgnoreHeaderForCacheReuse(header.keyAsHTTPHeaderName.value())
323 && header.value != oldHeaders.get(header.keyAsHTTPHeaderName.value()))
324 return false;
325 } else if (header.value != oldHeaders.get(header.key))
326 return false;
327 }
328
329 // For this second loop, we don't actually need to compare values, checking that the
330 // key is contained in newHeaders is sufficient due to the previous loop.
331 for (const auto& header : oldHeaders) {
332 if (header.keyAsHTTPHeaderName) {
333 if (!shouldIgnoreHeaderForCacheReuse(header.keyAsHTTPHeaderName.value())
334 && !newHeaders.contains(header.keyAsHTTPHeaderName.value()))
335 return false;
336 } else if (!newHeaders.contains(header.key))
337 return false;
338 }
339
340 return true;
341}
342
343void CachedRawResource::clear()
344{
345 m_data = nullptr;
346 setEncodedSize(0);
347 if (m_loader)
348 m_loader->clearResourceData();
349}

352void CachedRawResource::previewResponseReceived(const ResourceResponse& response)
353{
354 CachedResourceHandle<CachedRawResource> protectedThis(this);
355 CachedResource::previewResponseReceived(response);
356 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedRawResourceClient> w(m_clients);
357 while (CachedRawResourceClient* c = w.next())
